===Definition===
Region or governmental unit created by another country
and generally ruled by another country.

===Etymology===
Latin "colonia"; ultimately from Indo-European *qwel

===Pronunciation===
kol-o-ni

===Noun===
colony; plural: colonies

====Example====
Example:  Bermuda is a crown colony of Great Britain.

